The Post Mile is the mileage measured from the county line, or from the beginning of a route. Each postmile along a route in a county is a unique location on the state highway system.
A leg is given for each count location and is denoted by an A, B or O according to route direction.
B = back leg, A = ahead leg, and O = traffic volume is equal for the back and ahead legs.
